AB  - A self-consistent quantum transport simulation framework incorporating electron-electron and electron-photon interactions from first-principles is presented. It relies on density functional theory (DFT), the Non-equilibrium Green's function (NEGF) formalism, and the GW approximation to account for many-body effects. As application, a bulk-like InAs structure, configured both as n-type resistor and p-i-n photo-diode, is considered. We demonstrate that the developed approach can deliver accurate, beyond-DFT band gaps and captures the physics of impact ionization, light absorption, and photon-induced avalanche processes. It therefore allows to extract ab initio parameters such as optical absorption coefficients or impact ionization rates and to pass them to classical technology computer-aided design tools.
