AB  - Abstract: A large-scale computer simulation of the process of electronic excitation transport in close-packed nanoclusters of cadmium selenide colloidal quantum dots of various dimensions—one-dimensional, two-dimensional, and three-dimensional—has been performed. Quantitative dependences of the transport efficiency on a set of parameters characterizing the quantum dots have been obtained and analyzed. It has been shown that nonluminescent quantum dots and the thickness of the ligand shell have the greatest influence.
