AB  - Adv. Quantum Technol. 2022, 5, 2200013 DOI: 10.1002/qute.202200013 In the original published article the simulations of the effects of diagonal disorder incorrectly contained a factor of (1/2). This weakened the effects of diagonal errors, compared to the correctly simulated off-diagonal errors. Here, this issue is remedied by presenting the corrected effects of diagonal disorder. The corrected Figure 4(a), 5(a), and C1 can be found here. 4(a) Figure (Figure presented.) Fidelity peaks (Formula presented.) ((Formula presented.) against the state (Formula presented.) for (Formula presented.), (Formula presented.), and (Formula presented.)) for the routing protocol in the presence of diagonal disorder with different error scales (Formula presented.) and for random Gaussian and flat distributions (solid orange and dashed blue line, respectively). Each point has been averaged over 1000 realisations of the fidelity. 5(a) Figure (Figure presented.) EOF between sites 1 and 4 at (Formula presented.), (Formula presented.), and (Formula presented.) in the presence of diagonal disorder with different error scales (Formula presented.) and for random Gaussian and flat distributions (solid orange and dashed blue line, respectively). Each point has been averaged over 1000 realisations of the EOF. C1 Figure (Figure presented.) Left: Fidelity F1 against (Formula presented.) at (Formula presented.) in the presence of diagonal disorder. Right: Fidelity F1 against (Formula presented.) at (Formula presented.) in the presence of diagonal disorder. The orange line corresponds to the ideal case where there is no error. The dots are the averaged fidelity of 1000 fidelity realisations for each unknown phase with error scaled up to 30%. The angles are given in degrees. In addition: In section ‘Router Robustness’, the first and the second sentences of the second paragraph should read as: “A very robust behaviour of the fidelity against diagonal disorder can be seen in Figure 4(a) where the fidelity remains above 99% at (Formula presented.) and (Formula presented.) at a later time, (Formula presented.), even with large error scale, (Formula presented.). With significant error scale, (Formula presented.), the fidelity at (Formula presented.), (Formula presented.), and (Formula presented.) remains above 98%, 94%, and 88%, respectively”. The second sentence of the third paragraph should read as: “Both figures illustrate that when (Formula presented.), the routing fidelity remains above 97% at three consecutive times ((Formula presented.), (Formula presented.), and (Formula presented.)) with diagonal disorder, while it remains above 90% at the same three consecutive times with off-diagonal disorder”. In section ‘Entanglement Robustness’, the first and the second sentences of the second paragraph should read as: “We observe that the generation of the entangled state seems to be very robust against diagonal disorder, Figure 5a, with an EOF that remains above 99% at (Formula presented.) for error scale up to (Formula presented.) and above 95% for a significant error scale of (Formula presented.). Furthermore, the EOF at times up to (Formula presented.) remains above 90% with a relatively large error scale of (Formula presented.) ”. In section ‘Phase Sensor Protocol and Its Robustness’, the last sentence of the first paragraph should be modified to be: “The diagonal disorder on the other hand has very weak effect on the fidelity…”. The main conclusions of the paper are not affected by these modifications.
