AB  - X-ray / γ-ray detection and imaging have important applications in medical inspections,security monitoring,and noninvasive industrial detections. Comparison with the indirect conversion detection with scintillators,the direct conversion detection converting the X-ray / γ-ray photons into electron / hole pairs has higher quantum efficiency. However,the interaction of X-ray / γ-ray photons with solid target is quite complicated. It includes scattering, photoelectrical effect, Compton effect, pair productions, and etc.. Apart from this, the transportation of photon induced carriers is also complicated,including diffusion,drift,and recombination. Due to those complicated physical process,the simulation tool for the direct X-ray / γ-ray detector is seldom reported. In this article,a few simulation models are proposed to analyse the physical process of absorption of X-ray / γ-ray photons,and the transportation of carriers. As the comparison between the simulation results and experimental results shown,these simulation models can be used to simulate and design the X-ray / γ-ray detector accurately.
