AB  - The performance of the basic experimental (Al-ZnMgO/ZnMgO/CIGSSe) photovoltaic device has been enhanced here. This article uses the Methylammonium Lead Iodide (MAPbI3) crystal structure-based Perovskite absorber-2 as the hole transport layer (HTL) material. At the start of the work, CdS-free experimental photovoltaic devices are simulated. After simulation, photovoltaic results are successfully validated using the AFORS-HET tool by employing experimental optoelectronics data. Further, we have optimized the Al-ZnMgO as a transparent conducting oxide (TCO), buffer-ZnMgO, and absorber-CIGSSe layer thickness and doping density of the basic photovoltaic device. The performance parameters of the basic device have been improved. However, the external quantum efficiency (EQE) is still lower than that of the basic photovoltaic device due to the lack of HTL material. In addition, the optimized photovoltaic device incorporates Perovskite absorber-2 as an HTL material on the back side of the CIGSSe absorber-1 layer, resulting in a proposed CIGSSe/Perovskite inorganic and inorganic thin film solar cell (TFSC). The proposed photovoltaic device suppresses the photogenerated minority carrier recombination losses and absorbs the bulk of ultraviolet (UV) light. And that improves the photovoltaic parameters such as EQE, efficiency (η) = 27.95%, short-circuit current density (JSC) = 41.67 mA/cm2, open-circuit voltage (VOC) = 816.3 mV, and fill factor (FF) = 82.15%. The improved parameters are obtained by optimizing the band energy, thickness, doping density, and material defect trap density of the TCO, buffer, CIGSSe absorber-1, and Perovskite absorber-2 layers.
