AB  - Galena is the most common mineral of lead. Galena, PbS contains 86.5% Pb, 13.8% S mixed with other elements like silver, copper, zinc, cadmium, indium. Lead sulfide (PbS) crystallizes in the rock salt crystal structure and behaves as a semiconductor. In this research work thermoelectric properties of galena have been investigated through computer simulation using Density Functional Theory and Boltzmann transport equations. The Seebeck coefficient, electrical conductivity, thermal conductivity and figure of merit have been calculated using BoltzTraP tool based on Quantum Espresso code. Also, electronic band structures and elastic constants of galena have been calculated. Conclusions based on thermoelectric properties have been highlighted and compared with available results.
