AB  - The RF/DC performances of LG = 19 nm heterogeneous integrated Ga0.15In0.85As/InAs/Ga0.15In0.85As composite channel based InP HEMT (high electron mobility transistor) on Si (Silicon) wafer was investigated by using Sentaurus-TCAD simulations. In this research work, we systematically studied the impact of fixed negative charges (QF) at InP/SiO2 interface on the heterogeneous integrated transistor characteristics. The proposed heterogeneous integrated transistor on Si-wafer exhibited a transconductance (gm), drain current (IDS), fmax (maximum frequency of oscillation) and fT (cut-off frequency) of 1956 mS/mm, 1160 mA/mm, 576 GHz and 1138 GHz respectively with a QF of -5 × 1010/cm2 at InP/SiO2 interface. When QF was increased to -1 × 1012/cm2, gm, IDS, fT and fmax were degraded by 12%, 15%, 23.5% and 29.2% respectively due to the upward bending of EC (conduction band) energy level. The heterogeneous integrated Ga0.15In0.85As/InAs/Ga0.15In0.85As composite channel based InP HEMT on Si-substrate is considered as one of the most attractive transistors for future beyond 5G and quantum computing applications.
