AB  - <p> This paper presents theoretical research work for device simulation of solar cells based on Methylammonium lead iodide CH3NH3Pb(I <sub>1 − X</sub> Br <sub>x</sub> ) <sub>3</sub> concentration, band offsets, and other characteristics that have an impact on efficiency. SCAPs software is utilized to model and simulate the proposed solar cell. The results obtained of the proposed solar cell design have high efficiency of 36.44%. Copper iodide (CuI) as the hole transport material and Tin oxide (SnO2F) as the transparent conducting oxide are implemented in design to analyze the characteristics of perovskite solar cells (PSC). The results demonstrate that the proposed design have identical concepts but enhanced outcome compared to the existing one. The quantum efficiency curve depicts that the perovskite material has good absorption across the full visible spectrum. CH3NH3Pb(I <sub>1 − X</sub> Br <sub>x</sub> ) <sub>3</sub> solar cells are emerging as an important renewable energy source for current and future context. Research is being carried for enhancement in solar cell designs. </p>
