AB  - We propose a single-junction perovskite solar cell design using an ultra-thin transition metal dichalcogenide-based transport layers. We optimized the device performance with respect to the absorber thickness, defect densities, and transport layer thicknesses (electron and hole transport layers). Our simulation results indicate an excellent device performance with a high power conversion efficiency of approximately 33.7% alongside excellent key parameter values for the open-circuit voltage (Voc), short circuit current (Jsc), fill factor (FF), and quantum efficiency (QE). This work provides a guideline to design cost-effective, ecofriendly, and highly efficient perovskite solar cells.
