AB  - This paper presents the development of a deep learning model designed to identify six distinct types of Thai food dishes, using an imbalanced dataset with 2,736 images. To investigate and solve the imbalance issue, three approaches, consisting of undersampling, oversampling, and hybridsampling approaches, were applied before conducting the augmentation process and transformation. The processed data were then used to train three transfer learning models, consisting of ResNet50, MobileNet, and InceptionV3. The results indicate that the hybridsampling method can help improve the performance of each transfer learning model. Especially, the accuracy can be improved from 94% to 96% for the ResNet50 model.
