AB  - Nano-air-channel photodetectors (NACPDs) based on field emission have attracted much attention due to their ability to realize ballistic electron transport in the air. However, most of the previous NACPDs suffer from small photocurrent and low responsivity. Herein, we propose Si NACPDs with in-plane nano-air-channel, which can greatly improve the photocurrent and responsivity. The simulation results show that the electron collection efficiency of our in-plane NACPDs is as high as 96.5% and the transition time across the nano-air-channel is only about 100 fs. A CMOS compatible process is developed to prepare the Si NACPDs. A record photocurrent of 31.4 mA, together with a high responsivity of 2.3 A/W and a remarkable external quantum efficiency (EQE) of 336%, are experimentally achieved at 850 nm. This work provides a new promising candidate for efficient near ultraviolet to near infrared photodetectors.
