AB  - The AC/DC performance of AlGaN/GaN MOSHEMT using Al<inf>2</inf>O<inf>3</inf> as an oxide layer for varying AlN spacer layer thicknesses is examined. The simulation results show that the AlN spacer with a thickness of 1 nm outperforms spacers with thicknesses of 0.5, 1.5, and 2 nm in terms of transconductance and drain current. The quantum well depth and mobility behavior for different AlN spacer layer thicknesses were also observed to optimize the device performance. However, at a 2 nm AlN spacer layer thickness, the gate capacitance is significantly lower, resulting in a slightly higher cutoff frequency. These results revealed that different spacer layer thicknesses can affect the device&#x2019;s properties and provide insights for improving the device&#x2019;s performance. The device engineers can use these devices according to their specific application requirements.
