TI  - Kadanoff-Baym Equations for Interacting Systems with Dissipative Lindbladian Dynamics
LA  - eng
JF  - Physical Review Letters
VL  - 133
IS  - 6
PY  - 2024
SN  - 10797114, 00319007
PB  - American Physical Society
DO  - 10.1103/PhysRevLett.133.066901
AB  - The extraordinary quantum properties of nonequilibrium systems governed by dissipative dynamics have become a focal point in contemporary scientific inquiry. The nonequilibrium Green's functions (NEGF) theory provides a versatile method for addressing driven nondissipative systems, utilizing the powerful diagrammatic technique to incorporate correlation effects. We here present a second-quantization approach to the dissipative NEGF theory, reformulating Keldysh ideas to accommodate Lindbladian dynamics and extending the Kadanoff-Baym equations accordingly. Generalizing diagrammatic perturbation theory for many-body Lindblad operators, the formalism enables correlated and dissipative real-time simulations for the exploration of transient and steady-state changes in the electronic, transport, and optical properties of materials.
