DO  - 10.48550/arXiv.2410.07909
AB  - A quantum algorithm for simulating multidimensional scalar transport problems using a time-marching strategy is presented. After discretization, the explicit time-marching operator is separated into an advection-like component and a corrective shift operator. The advection-like component is mapped to a Hamiltonian simulation problem and is combined with the shift operator through the linear combination of unitaries algorithm. The result is an unscaled block encoding of the time-marching operator with an optimal success probability without the need for amplitude amplification, thereby retaining a linear dependence on the simulation time. State-vector simulations of a scalar transported in a steady two-dimensional Taylor-Green vortex support the theoretical findings.
