AB  - The photonic quantum spin Hall effect in time reversal invariant photonic system shows two pseudospin-up and-down photonic states preserved pseudo-time-reversal symmetry inC6v symmetry, and forms a typical of unidirectional helical edge modes within a topological bulk photonic bands gap. Here we demonstrate topological unidirectional helical edge states with robustness and pseudospin-locking in all-dielectric topological photonic crystals with honeycomb lattice. Based on intrinsic and local chirality of the topological helical edge modes, we calculate the directionality D to characterize directionality of topological unidirectional helical edge modes. The unidirectional excitation of topological helical edge states is position-dependent of chiral source, which is checked out by the full-wave simulations. A specific multifunctional waveguide with tunable cross-channel, V-splitting and four-channel in a waveguide structure with cross-like route is achieved by changing the location of chiral source based on chirality map. A reprogrammable system to recode information (pseudospin-polarized and location) of chiral source is presented by us, and realize multi-switching for integrated photonic via circuits external circuits control in computer. Our work has great potential for applications in on-chip optical circuits with recoding and modularized information processing using pseudospin-dependent one-way transport.
